<h4>Welcome to the CTCMA Safety Program Examination Site</h4>
<p>In order to register for CTCMA registration you are required to pass a Safety Program examination. There are four types of Safety Program examinations and applicants are required to pass the examinations respective to the class of registration they are applying for.</p>
<p>Detailed information regarding the Safety Program Examination is available in the <a href=" http://ctcma.bc.ca/assets/files/pdf_resources/Safety/Safety_Program_Examination_Guide-rev1.pdf"> Safety Program Examination Guide </a>.</p>
<p>In order to sit the examination you must nominate a CTCMA approved invigilator who will supervise you during the examination. A list of approved invigilators is available <a href="<?php echo site_url('main/invigilators'); ?>">here.</a>.</p>
